rch-history-jesus-christ/"><img data-chromatic="ignore" alt="" style="aspect-ratio:1.51;background-color:#F6F6F6" class="c-image" loading="lazy" src="https://www.thechurchnews.com/resizer/v2/GQQMAEWDJ5EV7KS7QFJKEKHDQY.JPG?focal=1781%2C404&amp;auth=1f7f49f56bd7672ff8e13c70ea01c2e0065557b070bbae8923de550a9418b15f&amp;width=190&amp;height=126" srcSet="https://www.thechurchnews.com/resizer/v2/GQQMAEWDJ5EV7KS7QFJKEKHDQY.JPG?focal=1781%2C404&amp;auth=1f7f49f56bd7672ff8e13c70ea01c2e0065557b070bbae8923de550a9418b15f&amp;width=380&amp;height=252 2x" width="190" height="126"/></a></div></div><div class="col-9"><div class="page-promo__category"><a class="link" href="https://www.thechurchnews.com/history-archive/">Church History</a></div><div class="page-promo__title"><a class="link" href="https://www.thechurchnews.com/history-archive/2026/06/26/new-nauvoo-temple-visitors-center-bridges-church-history-jesus-christ/">New Nauvoo Temple Visitors’ Center bridges early Church history and house of the Lord to Jesus Christ</a></div><div class="page-promo__byline">By<!-- --> <div class="page-promo__author"><a href="https://www.thechurchnews.com/authors/trent-toone/" class="author-profile-link">Trent Toone</a></div><div class="page-promo__date"><span class="line"></span><time dateTime="2026-06-26T21:00:00Z" class="date-published date-published--iso">Published 13 hours ago</time></div></div><div class="page-promo__description">Before the center&#x27;s dedication, Matt Grow and Juanita Coleman discuss the purpose behind the new Nauvoo Temple Visitors&#x27; Center and its exhibits.</div></div></div><div class="row"><div class="col"><hr/></div></div><div class="row page-promo"><div class="col-3"><div class="page-promo__media mx-auto mb-1 mb-lg-0"><a class="page-promo__link" href="https://www.thechurchnews.com/temples/2026/06/26/salt-lake-temple-celebration-resources-involve-members-around-globe/"><img data-chromatic="ignore" alt="" style="aspect-ratio:1.51;background-color:#F6F6F6" class="c